{
  "page": "Daeryssa",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Princess</span><br />Daeryssa</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Prince\" title=\"Prince\">Princess</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>Princess <b>Daeryssa </b> is a character in a song. According to the songs, she was once saved by <a href=\"/index.php/Serwyn_of_the_Mirror_Shield\" title=\"Serwyn of the Mirror Shield\">Serwyn of the Mirror Shield</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Giants\" title=\"Giants\">giants</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Daeryssa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Given the typical <a href=\"/index.php/High_Valyrian\" title=\"High Valyrian\">High Valyrian</a> spelling of Daeryssa's name, it is possible <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a> had intended for Daeryssa to be a <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">Targaryen</a> princess when he first introduced Serwyn as a member of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> in <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> However, <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> revealed that Serwyn was actually a legendary hero from the <a href=\"/index.php/Age_of_Heroes\" title=\"Age of Heroes\">Age of Heroes</a> that singers claim to be a Kingsguard despite the fact that the institution was not created until <a href=\"/index.php/10_AC\" title=\"10 AC\">10&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_age_of_heroes.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_age_of_heroes.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Daeryssa's historical status has not been mentioned. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Daeryssa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_15\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 15\">Chapter 15</a>, Sansa I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_8\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 8\">Chapter 8</a>, Bran II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_age_of_heroes.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_age_of_heroes.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Ancient History: The Age of Heroes.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404012214\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.074 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.276 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 556/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10477/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 3771/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 399/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 8/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1575/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.180/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.46 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  268.913      1 -total\n 94.15%  253.192      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 93.40%  251.154      1 Template:Infobox\n 12.50%   33.627     12 Template:Infobox_value\n  4.39%   11.802      3 Template:Info